						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājarāja III. Date Lost.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription records the gift of 1/4 <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> of land, in Vikramaśōḻaṉ-Kaḍambūr left in the hands of the <hi rend="italic">śivabrāhmaṇas</hi> of the temple, by Maṇaṟkkuḍaiyā[ṉ] ••of Iḍaiyaḷa-nāḍu in Kulōttuṅgaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu, for burning a perpetual lamp. Other details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
